<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="599" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,219,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="599">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,731,755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="599">Comments.</emphasis>
An attempt was made to dissect the material but after considerable time in a humidification chamber the apical metasomal segments were unrelenting and we opted to refrain from further manipulation less the specimen become damaged. It is greatly hoped that extensive sampling of bees in 
<collectingCountry box="[468,626,827,851]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="4" pageNumber="599">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic might bring forth additional material, including females, so that the species can be more fully characterized and compared with its congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
